In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate with sweetened condensed milk. In small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over water; let stand 1 minute. Over low heat, stir until gelatin dissolves. Combine gelatin and chocolate mixture. Add vanilla. Cool to room temperature. Fold in whipped cream. Spread into crust. Chill 3 hours or until set. Garnish with additional whipped cream. Store leftovers covered in refrigerator.